comments.body:
@shibumi Like I mentioned in https://github.com/containers/podman/issues/27499 already we do not support such User/Group= setups and most of these systemd hardening options are fundamentally incompatible with podman since you block podman from doing what it has to do.

Now of course podman commands should not panic so there is certainly something wrong in the code that should be fixed here. But in general don't' expect this stuff to work or our help debugging issues caused by such units.

I am not sure if mixing the systemd cgroup unit management with the podman cgroups driver is a good idea at all. Having two process trying to configure the cgroups can certainly cause issues.
